Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.83,0:12:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the free enterprise system then,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.93,0:12:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,which benefits all of society.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.63,0:12:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's no point of demonizing industry
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.03,0:13:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,when what you wear is made by industry,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.33,0:13:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,what you eat is made by industry,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.13,0:13:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,your haircut is done through industry,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.53,0:13:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,your eyeglasses are industry,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.73,0:13:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you're breathing in and out through
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.53,0:13:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,what's produced by industry,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.73,0:13:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you're standing at what introduce,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.93,0:13:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and here's the building produced by industry,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.93,0:13:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,speaking on the microphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.13,0:13:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what about your debt to industry?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.03,0:13:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear God, I give thanks for industry
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.53,0:13:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and what it has provided for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.73,0:13:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Look what I've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.93,0:13:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,All I do is stand here and I benefit,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.81,0:13:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, by the efforts of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.81,0:13:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,generation after generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.61,0:13:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all of us are blessed by this sweat and output,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.81,0:13:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the suffering of all the generations that preceded us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.01,0:13:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We take for granted what to another person
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.21,0:13:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,would be miraculous,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.41,0:13:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's still denied to two-thirds of the world at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.14,0:13:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Those people that we were looking at the map,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.67,0:13:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,can't go and buy this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.37,0:13:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been in their country.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.47,0:13:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been in the favelas on the side of the mountain
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.27,0:13:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in Brazil, in Rio de Janeiro,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.09,0:13:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,where if you've got a couple of strings and a twig
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.49,0:14:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and an old rag,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.79,0:14:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and maybe the top of a piece of tin can,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.99,0:14:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that's where you and your 12 brothers and sisters live.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.38,0:14:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You take turns sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.79,0:14:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The favela is on the side of the mountain,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.92,0:14:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and there on the side of the mountain
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.32,0:14:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is the great statue of Jesus Christ looking over all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.26,0:14:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, before you curse American industry,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.40,0:14:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,look at its opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.84,0:14:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at its opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.84,0:14:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Starvation, malnutrition, agony, suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.90,0:14:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no medicine for their sickness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.60,0:14:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no codeine to make their broken leg feel better.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.19,0:14:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.36,0:14:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we can be grateful to our own culture,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.96,0:14:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,our own society.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.30,0:14:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We can be grateful for it and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.50,0:14:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,it's got chocolate and vanilla,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.20,0:14:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and it doesn't fly without wings,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.26,0:14:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but it doesn't necessarily have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.06,0:14:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll serve us for the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.03,0:15:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's the anti-corporate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.53,0:15:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the DNA promise of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.23,0:15:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.73,0:15:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We just took it out of local ads.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.63,0:15:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It said 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.23,0:15:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You see these things on television,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.73,0:15:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the telephone psychics who get on there and give you a reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.33,0:15:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Right off the bat, they calibrate it at 95.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.03,0:15:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,At $20 a minute,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.43,0:15:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,their job is to keep you on the phone as long as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.03,0:15:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and get you intrigued with these wonderful stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.15,0:15:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,New Age shamanism is very iffy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.91,0:15:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And here was another local.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.41,0:15:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just a local ad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.71,0:15:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time I see a quarter pager,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.11,0:15:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of fancy jabberish about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.71,0:15:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I know where about it's going to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.11,0:15:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And schools that teach shamanic magic again are also
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.20,0:15:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,questionable.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.80,0:15:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.10,0:15:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're appealing to superstition.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.59,0:15:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,People think spiritual means the occult, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.79,0:15:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Mysteries and magical things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.79,0:16:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They are impressed by the so-called miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.68,0:16:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the miraculous, first of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.77,0:16:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is not something you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.62,0:16:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't anybody that performs the miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.72,0:16:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nobody that performs the miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.94,0:16:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens is this lady sits down across from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.84,0:16:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,She's paralyzed on one side.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.97,0:16:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know why she's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.94,0:16:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Friends look over at you expectantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.24,0:16:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And then telepathically, you get what they're hoping for.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.15,0:16:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You look back at the lady and she either gets better
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.65,0:16:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,or she doesn't get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.35,0:16:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If she gets better, then the stories go out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.72,0:16:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got nothing to do with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.62,0:16:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That energy plus her karma is transformative.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.39,0:16:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And the miraculous occurs or it doesn't occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.09,0:16:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But it does so of its own nature
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.99,0:16:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as the effect of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.90,0:16:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a field effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.40,0:16:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,See, there's no you that performs a miracle
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.00,0:16:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's dualistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.80,0:17:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The field then brings about into manifestation
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.50,0:17:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the potentiality which is karmically there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.53,0:17:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And she looks at you and she smiles
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.33,0:17:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and you realize that she's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.60,0:17:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.40,0:17:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that the way to God is through joy, givingness, surrender,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.06,0:17:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,saying no to selfishness, personal gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.49,0:17:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If a hundred people genuflect when you walk by,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.79,0:17:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,watch out because you're that spiritual ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.29,0:17:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to be alert for it at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.09,0:17:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Alert for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.06,0:17:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, because the more involved you become,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.06,0:17:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the more attractive you become to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.23,0:17:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,People think that they're in love with and attracted to and love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.34,0:17:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're naive, you will believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.00,0:17:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's the presence of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.04,0:17:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Within you that they are in love with.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.69,0:17:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the presence of God within you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.39,0:18:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You see reflected back to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.08,0:18:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not the mirror that you're in love with.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.72,0:18:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And many of these fell because they fell in love with the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.84,0:18:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And the teacher thought, took personally the adulation on a personal basis
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.84,0:18:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of seeing that the worshipers were worshiping the presence of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.44,0:18:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which you are only.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.24,0:18:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,An avenue to think that it's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.70,0:18:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if you do the Course in Miracles,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.00,0:18:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you will see people will be far more attracted to you than they used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.50,0:18:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They want to be in your presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.90,0:18:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They feel high, they feel joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.54,0:18:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And the idea would naturally be it's because of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.72,0:18:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me, Pete or me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.42,0:18:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan is doing that to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.62,0:18:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's the presence of God within.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.02,0:19:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've removed the barriers to the presence of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.72,0:19:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And now that is what they're attracted to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.52,0:19:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not attracted to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.22,0:19:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the same idiot you always were.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.92,0:19:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,As proven by all the fallen gurus.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.82,0:19:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.62,0:19:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You were the same idiot you always were.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.02,0:19:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't know any better.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.02,0:19:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You thought it was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.18,0:19:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, golly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.18,0:19:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.41,0:19:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.71,0:19:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's look at some of the better things of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.15,0:19:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The great cathedrals.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.45,0:19:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Westminster Abbey,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.55,0:19:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Chartres Cathedral,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.65,0:19:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Notre Dame.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.13,0:19:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,All 790.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.63,0:19:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The great Buddha of Coyota,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.23,0:19:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,780.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.13,0:19:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The Taj Mahal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.53,0:19:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sheer beauty alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.53,0:19:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,750.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.53,0:19:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The Alhambra.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.53,0:19:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This is misspelled.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.53,0:19:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The Alhambra.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.03,0:19:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.53,0:19:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A-L-H-A-M-B-R-A.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.03,0:19:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,720.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.03,0:19:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Basilica of Saint Peter in Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.13,0:19:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,710.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.40,0:19:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Beneath the Basilica of Saint Peter are some relics
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.47,0:19:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of one of the great apostles.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.04,0:20:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And we asked, are they true relics?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.04,0:20:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answer is yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.04,0:20:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They are indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.54,0:20:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Much like the relics that came through here of the Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.04,0:20:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,turned out to be 900.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.38,0:20:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The Chapel of the Holy Cross here in Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.38,0:20:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,565.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.38,0:20:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder it's attractive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.88,0:20:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The Ganges River by sheer worship of the Hindu followers is 560.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.01,0:20:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Stonehenge, 599.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.01,0:20:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The Vatican itself, 570.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.51,0:20:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pieta, 590.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.01,0:20:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Angkor Wat, 550.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.51,0:20:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Lourdes, 510.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.51,0:20:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Pyramids of Egypt, 520.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.51,0:20:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Great Sphinx, 520.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.99,0:20:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's another misspelling.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.49,0:20:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It should be the Great Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.99,0:20:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,now, which the Afghanis blew up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.59,0:20:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The Great Buddha in Afghanistan,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.09,0:20:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,which was the biggest in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.59,0:20:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,did calibrate at 555.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.13,0:20:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,St. Patrick's Cathedral in New York City, 530.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.18,0:21:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the biggest cathedral,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.68,0:21:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the biggest church, the cathedral in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.68,0:21:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the Cathedral of St. John the Divine in New York City,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.68,0:21:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,which is still unfinished,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.18,0:21:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,even though they've been at it 100 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.87,0:21:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is 530.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.87,0:21:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The Washington National Cathedral,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.37,0:21:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,which Betty was telling us about.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.87,0:21:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,She said it was exquisite, 530.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.25,0:21:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Ramana Maharshi's Ananchula Mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.25,0:21:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't pronounce it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.75,0:21:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He always had thought there was something divine
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.91,0:21:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,about that mountain,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.91,0:21:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and never left it his whole life.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.91,0:21:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrated at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.10,0:21:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you who have been to Machu Picchu,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.10,0:21:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it's at 510.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.49,0:21:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you who have been to see
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.49,0:21:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the Great Temple at Karnak, 415.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.49,0:21:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The Crystal Cathedral in L.A. is 410.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.95,0:21:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The Sakya Monastery in Tibet, 390.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.45,0:21:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Lhasa, what is the energy of Lhasa itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.70,0:21:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Currently, 320.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.66,0:21:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we come to what people give up so much,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.16,0:21:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach Mecca and Medina,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.66,0:22:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the holy cities of Islam, 205 and 225.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.90,0:22:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd be better to go up Mount Everest.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.40,0:22:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,460.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.40,0:22:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The Relics of Christian Saints, 750.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.66,0:22:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinto Shrine, 650.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.66,0:22:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Tibetan Buddhist stupa in Sedona, Arizona,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.17,0:22:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is already 640,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.17,0:22:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,which is quite amazing, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.79,0:22:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right here in Sedona, 640.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.79,0:22:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we in Sedona?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.79,0:22:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yeah, we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.79,0:22:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.18,0:22:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Relics of the Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.18,0:22:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,we as a class went out and calibrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.68,0:22:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We calibrated in class,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.18,0:22:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and we found out what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.18,0:22:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We all left class and went over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.68,0:22:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We said, I think it's 905,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.68,0:22:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going there and visit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.18,0:22:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It was true.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.68,0:22:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.68,0:22:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the Relics of Saint Peter,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.68,0:22:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,allegedly under the floor of the Basilica in Rome,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.28,0:22:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually a fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.28,0:22:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and they do, in fact, calibrate at 910.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.53,0:23:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There's two relics we've been able to verify,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.03,0:23:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the Buddha and, amazingly, Saint Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.36,0:23:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, contrasting calibrations,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.86,0:23:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,out of spiritual curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.86,0:23:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to stop in exactly five minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.36,0:23:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and take a break,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.36,0:23:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and after that, we'll have questions and answers
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.86,0:23:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and allow for recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.11,0:23:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The Shroud of Turin is a true relic.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.61,0:23:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It says no.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.11,0:23:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Crop circles are due to extraterrestrials.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.11,0:23:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It says no.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.90,0:23:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Crop circles are actually a human product.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.40,0:23:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It says yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.90,0:23:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Area 51 in Nevada,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.19,0:23:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's always on TV,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.69,0:23:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,with its spook music,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.69,0:23:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Area 51 in Nevada is actually only 201.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.54,0:23:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.81,0:23:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So, some things we did discover of interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.31,0:23:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, Area 51 is not, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.31,0:23:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,85 or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.31,0:23:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's not full of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.50,0:23:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,secret aliens and their secret weapons or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.50,0:23:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's an imaginary program there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.10,0:23:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.60,0:23:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The Easter Island statues are a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.60,0:24:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody ever really knew what they were.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.60,0:24:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,People have mystified about them,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.60,0:24:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and we calibrated them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.10,0:24:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just do it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.60,0:24:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Want to do them?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.60,0:24:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.10,0:24:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.60,0:24:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't want to do them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.20,0:24:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The Easter Island statues actually come out at 70.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.20,0:24:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,These are these big monolithic things that face out to sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.70,0:24:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.20,0:24:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If you read about,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.20,0:24:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.20,0:24:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If you read about the history of the Easter Islands,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.20,0:24:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,what preceded that,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.20,0:24:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and then now you get why they're 70.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.51,0:24:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very interesting story.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.01,0:24:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The society that lived on Easter Island
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.51,0:24:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,ate up everything and everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.01,0:24:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,until it was all gone and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.51,0:24:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are the,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.31,0:24:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,so we don't know anything about it except that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.50,0:24:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,they were 70.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.19,0:24:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Current Bethlehem,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.19,0:24:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,people, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.69,0:24:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,go to great sacrifice to visit the Holy Lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.19,0:24:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.90,0:25:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Current Bethlehem is at 70.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.40,0:25:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerusalem is at 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.90,0:25:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Holy Lands in general are at 70.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.68,0:25:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Israel 190,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.18,0:25:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Palestine 185.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.68,0:25:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And you would do better to go to the playground in Central Park
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.68,0:25:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,which is at least 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.57,0:25:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's obvious why those energies are so far down
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.57,0:25:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because they've been the focus of hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.07,0:25:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hatred, jihad, and all the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.24,0:25:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The U.S. court ruling under God
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.24,0:25:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,violates the First Amendment is false.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.32,0:25:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It does not violate the First Amendment.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.32,0:25:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But the energy that we'd like to see that come about
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.27,0:25:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is at 185 which is non-integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.27,0:25:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's remember then simply
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.74,0:25:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that the way to spiritual truth is through
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.81,0:25:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the joy of the source of one's own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.86,0:25:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't come from elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.16,0:26:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes from the knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.09,0:26:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that existence would not be possible
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.09,0:26:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,were it not for the source of one's own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.09,0:26:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And the proof of the existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.83,0:26:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the proof of the existence of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.33,0:26:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and the proof of the reality of God
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.83,0:26:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is your own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.33,0:26:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,For nothing can come into existence
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.83,0:26:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,except out of creation
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.92,0:26:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which requires a creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.19,0:26:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll take a break
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.19,0:26:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and then after the break
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.19,0:26:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll have questions and answers
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.19,0:26:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and any further discussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.19,0:26:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thank you for your forbearance
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.69,0:26:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and patience this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.69,0:26:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,For some of you it was a bit of a trial
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.19,0:26:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but we'll all survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.54,0:26:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So we've done enough presentation of data.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.54,0:26:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody is in a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.04,0:26:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,overwhelm.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.61,0:26:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore I thought we would just
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.61,0:26:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,do questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.61,0:26:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the end of which time
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.65,0:26:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be happy to greet all of you who
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.15,0:27:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,came and wanted to greet me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.65,0:27:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.00,0:27:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,design books, whatever, like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.42,0:27:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, the number of questions
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.92,0:27:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that the mind can manufacture are endless.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.28,0:27:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,To begin with, we will
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.78,0:27:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,answer a lot of questions at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.78,0:27:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no answer to the question why.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.48,0:27:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The question why requires omnipotence.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.59,0:27:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you're omnipotent
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.82,0:27:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you know that the question why is unanswerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.82,0:27:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.77,0:27:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it exists only as a mentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.20,0:27:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,When people ask why this, why that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.22,0:27:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because that's how evolution came out
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.22,0:27:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in a certain expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.22,0:27:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,People ask, for instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.62,0:28:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is ADHD
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.62,0:28:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,a spiritual condition or is it a medical condition
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.12,0:28:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,for which you need medication?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.53,0:28:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Having treated thousands,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.53,0:28:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I would say,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.25,0:28:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a medical condition that requires medication
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.38,0:28:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,without which the child will suffer rejection,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.38,0:28:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,guilt, anxiety,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.02,0:28:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,will be punished, ridiculed by their children, excluded.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.40,0:28:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be so savaged
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.40,0:28:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,by the side effects of the disorder
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.90,0:28:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's not worth having the disorder.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.90,0:28:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it was a spiritual condition,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.32,0:28:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be karmic, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.32,0:28:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.37,0:28:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,although there's some,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.55,0:28:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I think, a popular book that popularizes
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.55,0:28:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,some particular view of it, non-medical,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.55,0:28:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,being both spiritual and medical
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.29,0:28:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and a psychiatrist for 50 years, I would say,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.29,0:28:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with my child, I would put him on medication
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.80,0:29:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that would allow him to be normal
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.30,0:29:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so that he can operate at his fullest capacity.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.80,0:29:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's nothing special about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.99,0:29:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,People tend to make something special about ADHD.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.49,0:29:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've got diabetes, you take insulin.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.56,0:29:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, if you've got other disorders,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.06,0:29:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you take something for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.06,0:29:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've got asthma, you take antispasmodic.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.06,0:29:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what is so special about ADHD?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.06,0:29:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see anything uniquely special about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.56,0:29:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Without it, the child is obviously going to fail,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.98,0:29:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,feel guilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.77,0:29:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,sense of inferiority.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.77,0:29:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens is they end up traumatized
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.82,0:29:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,by the consequence, not as a result of the consequence,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.20,0:29:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, not as a result of the disorder,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.70,0:29:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but as a result of the social impact of the disorder.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.13,0:29:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The same is stuttering.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.33,0:29:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You have knowledge of stuttering,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.83,0:29:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but you have years of being ridiculed for being stuttering.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.33,0:29:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if there was a pill that cured stuttering,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.36,0:29:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I would take it, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.86,0:30:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the purpose of a disorder when...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.58,0:30:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the evolution of consciousness, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.08,0:30:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as it evolves into medical,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.08,0:30:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say medicine is part of the good karmic,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.58,0:30:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic inheritance of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.58,0:30:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that he no longer suffers from the things
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.58,0:30:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,which he used to suffer from.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.08,0:30:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the diseases that I studied and treated
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.08,0:30:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and was responsible for in the early days,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.58,0:30:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in my own early days of medicine,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.58,0:30:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,no longer even exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.08,0:30:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't kill anybody because they aren't even there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.08,0:30:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody dies of diphtheria or typhoid
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.08,0:30:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or any of the things that used to come in and die on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.58,0:30:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Dehydrate and be dead before you could get back to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.14,0:30:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there seems to be a positive karmic inheritance of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.14,0:30:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,as a result, I think, of the evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.64,0:30:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual work of all, of everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.14,0:30:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,lifts all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.20,0:30:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And the karmic inheritance is
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.70,0:31:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we keep discovering new cures for new things all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.40,0:31:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have a couple of patients
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.40,0:31:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,who have never recovered from a couple of simple things.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.90,0:31:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And I tell them,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.40,0:31:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,at the rate at which the pharmaceutical industry
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.40,0:31:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is pouring money into these discoveries,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.40,0:31:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,don't forget,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.40,0:31:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,every single common ailment
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.40,0:31:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is worth multi-millions, if not billions of dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.40,0:31:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be sure they're going to find a cure for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.40,0:31:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, just hang on until the cure appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.40,0:31:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I try to energize that thought form
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.43,0:31:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that a cure for whatever you're not recovered from so far
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.43,0:31:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,will appear, will appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.93,0:31:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's how things appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.43,0:31:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They're held as a possibility in human consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.46,0:31:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,out of compassion
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.56,0:31:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for the suffering of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.56,0:31:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And that, in that way, they tend to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.62,0:31:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the doctors in the audience,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.62,0:31:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,remember, most of the things,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.62,0:31:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't see syphilis anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.62,0:31:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,People waiting in line for injections with arsenic.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.78,0:31:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They used to be lined up around the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.78,0:32:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The veterans took arsenic shots
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.78,0:32:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and other doctors for hopeless syphilis.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.78,0:32:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And general Parasitis of the Insane
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.78,0:32:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,was the first mental disorder I had treated.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.78,0:32:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The Milwaukee County Asylum for the Insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.97,0:32:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It was called, it was called
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.71,0:32:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the Milwaukee County Asylum for the Insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.71,0:32:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the name of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.71,0:32:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't deal in euphemisms in those days.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.90,0:32:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, I also interned at the Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.90,0:32:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,for the Ruptured and Crippled in Brooklyn.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.90,0:32:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the name of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.90,0:32:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hospital for the Ruptured and Crippled.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.90,0:32:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, there wasn't this
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.35,0:32:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling uncomfortable neurotic sensitivity
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.35,0:32:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that pervades people now, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.35,0:32:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't mention if you're male or female
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.35,0:32:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,or if you're short or long
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.35,0:32:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,or what your religion is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.35,0:32:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,or how far you went to school, all those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.35,0:32:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody's going to get,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.35,0:32:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,feel uncomfortable about it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.35,0:32:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a book out now called
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.73,0:32:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,something called The Thought Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.73,0:33:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.37,0:33:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,How these big publishing houses screen,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.37,0:33:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,especially in the academic world,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.37,0:33:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,anything that might be taken as offensive by anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.37,0:33:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So, their books are getting smaller and smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.47,0:33:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Find them before like four or five pages
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.47,0:33:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because something everywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.47,0:33:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to make somebody nervous, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.47,0:33:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That is really your problem
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.72,0:33:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and to project it onto society, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.72,0:33:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of the great
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.36,0:33:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,less than integrous movements of current society, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.65,0:33:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If something makes me uncomfortable,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.65,0:33:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to remove God from any mention in society
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.65,0:33:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because it makes some people uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.65,0:33:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It never dawns on them that removing God
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.16,0:33:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,from any reference in society makes me uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.16,0:33:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.16,0:33:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that removing it makes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.16,0:33:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,70% of the population uncomfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.16,0:33:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't dawn on the egocentric person
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.16,0:33:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,who says, because it makes me comfortable,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.16,0:33:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,all street cars should be removed from the streets,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.16,0:34:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,all buses should stop, train whistles should stop
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.16,0:34:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because it makes me uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.80,0:34:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The people that are made uncomfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.00,0:34:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,by the factual events in society
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.03,0:34:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,need a psychiatrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.03,0:34:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we're for.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.03,0:34:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's who we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.19,0:34:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we're for, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.19,0:34:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If it makes you uncomfortable,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.19,0:34:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,call us up.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.19,0:34:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.05,0:34:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,psychiatrists make a lot of people uncomfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.05,0:34:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm sure they would like to...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.24,0:34:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.24,0:34:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,people who don't see a psychiatrist and need to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.24,0:34:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,make a lot of other people uncomfortable, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.24,0:34:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes me uncomfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.01,0:34:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is people who are made uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.42,0:34:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel very uncomfortable about
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.42,0:34:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,people that are always uncomfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.87,0:34:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,because you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.87,0:34:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to make them uncomfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.87,0:34:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in just a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.35,0:34:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Even mentioning that there's people
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.35,0:34:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,who are made uncomfortable by everything
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.35,0:34:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,already makes them uncomfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.48,0:35:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're going to complain
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.48,0:35:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask for a new law
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.48,0:35:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to block people from making references
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.48,0:35:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to people who get uncomfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.48,0:35:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,because to do so makes them uncomfortable,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.37,0:35:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.37,0:35:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So we end up into this
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.76,0:35:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,securitas non sensibility
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.88,0:35:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,which keeps the trial lawyers societies going.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.88,0:35:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have some questions
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.07,0:35:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and hopefully some answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.96,0:35:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the cause of addiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.64,0:35:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,chemical and behavioral,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.64,0:35:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and what is the solution?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.12,0:35:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Good God.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.12,0:35:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer to that is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.92,0:35:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to go to an Al-Anon meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.92,0:35:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and they'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.92,0:35:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There's genetic, karmic,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.98,0:35:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,has to do with brain chemistry,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.98,0:35:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,has to do with genes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.98,0:35:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Both addiction and depression
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.30,0:35:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,are genetically linked.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.30,0:35:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A family with a lot of depression
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.30,0:35:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,also usually has a good deal of addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.30,0:36:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're very often crossed.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.91,0:36:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.74,0:36:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,having treated 10,000 alcoholics
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.74,0:36:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and I knew Bill Wilson
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.32,0:36:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,back many years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.32,0:36:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and then ran a clinic in the East
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.32,0:36:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,where we treated tens of thousands,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.32,0:36:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,literally.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.64,0:36:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And out here,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.37,0:36:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,one day a week,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.37,0:36:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I spent all day one day a week
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.37,0:36:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,for 10 years treating addiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.37,0:36:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So from that experiential background,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.37,0:36:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,one can say
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.37,0:36:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,there certainly seems to be a genetic disorder.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.37,0:36:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It certainly runs in families
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.37,0:36:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's certainly
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.37,0:36:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,a lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.37,0:36:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's certainly
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.37,0:36:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the rate of addiction increases
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.37,0:36:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,as your ancestors come
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.37,0:36:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,closer and closer to the North Pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.37,0:36:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If your ancestors come from Scandinavia,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.69,0:36:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the likelihood is extremely higher
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.69,0:36:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,than if they come from Italy
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.69,0:36:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,or Spain
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.69,0:36:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,or they're in the Mediterranean.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.69,0:36:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's genetic, ethnic,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.72,0:36:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure there's karmic reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.79,0:36:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.79,0:36:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I know a number of people
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.79,0:37:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,who died of alcoholism
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.79,0:37:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,one death after another
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.79,0:37:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and finally,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.79,0:37:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.17,0:37:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I know of one
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.17,0:37:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and the sixth round
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.17,0:37:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of the lifetime of addiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.17,0:37:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they finally surrendered it to God
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.17,0:37:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and became sober.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.43,0:37:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.43,0:37:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,sobriety was not accomplishable
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.43,0:37:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,before the 1940s.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.43,0:37:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody ever recovered from alcoholism.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.84,0:37:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they did,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.84,0:37:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,they were such an oddity
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.84,0:37:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that they were written up
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.84,0:37:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,as sort of a medical oddity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.84,0:37:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And we owe the recovery from addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.68,0:37:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to the humility
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.68,0:37:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Swiss psychoanalyst,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.68,0:37:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Carl Jung.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.03,0:37:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when Roland,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.03,0:37:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,who was well-to-do,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.03,0:37:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,went to see Carl Jung
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.28,0:37:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in Switzerland for psychoanalysis,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.28,0:37:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,he finally stopped drinking
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.28,0:37:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and went back to America.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.08,0:37:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,After a short time,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.08,0:37:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Roland got drunk again
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.08,0:37:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and became severely depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.08,0:37:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And he went back to see Carl Jung
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.08,0:37:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in Switzerland.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.08,0:37:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jung,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.24,0:38:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we all are thankful for his humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.24,0:38:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He says,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.24,0:38:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,alas, unfortunately,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.24,0:38:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,neither my art
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.24,0:38:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,nor my science
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.24,0:38:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,can be of help to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.24,0:38:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.24,0:38:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it has been reported
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.24,0:38:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,from time to time
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.24,0:38:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout history
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.24,0:38:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that there are those
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.24,0:38:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,who have thrown themselves wholeheartedly
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.24,0:38:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,into some spiritual organization
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.24,0:38:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and they have recovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.24,0:38:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I think at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.69,0:38:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Roland was an atheist,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.69,0:38:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,so it was not exactly great news.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.69,0:38:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Roland came back to America
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.69,0:38:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and he discovered the group
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.69,0:38:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that formed the essence
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.69,0:38:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 12 Steps of AA.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.69,0:38:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what the name
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.69,0:38:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of the group was at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.69,0:38:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And Roland threw himself
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.43,0:38:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,wholeheartedly
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.43,0:38:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,into this spiritual group
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.62,0:38:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to surrender everything to God
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.62,0:38:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and to make it honestly,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.68,0:38:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,honesty, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.68,0:38:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What became,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.68,0:38:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think there were at that time
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.68,0:38:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,only eight steps,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.68,0:38:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,they became eventually 12.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.78,0:38:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And Roland conveyed this
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.78,0:38:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to Evie,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.78,0:38:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,who recovered,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.78,0:38:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and Evie then gave the message
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.78,0:38:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to Bill W.,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.78,0:39:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,who scoffed at it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.20,0:39:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and said it was ridiculous
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.20,0:39:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,because Bill was an atheist
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.61,0:39:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was not ready
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.61,0:39:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to hear anything
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.61,0:39:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,about the God business.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.61,0:39:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And he told Evie,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.61,0:39:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,don't come back
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.61,0:39:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,about this God business.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.61,0:39:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And then Bill
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.61,0:39:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,had a great black despair
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.61,0:39:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and he listened
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.61,0:39:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to whatever he had said.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.61,0:39:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And being an atheist
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.61,0:39:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.61,0:39:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,he surrendered
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.61,0:39:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to only what he could assume
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.64,0:39:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,would be God.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.64,0:39:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And that went through
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.64,0:39:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,a profound transformation
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.64,0:39:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the room lit up
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.64,0:39:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,with a holy light.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.64,0:39:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.96,0:39:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of that moment
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.96,0:39:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,has saved millions of lives
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.96,0:39:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and will save millions more.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.96,0:39:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.96,0:39:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what it's all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.96,0:39:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.67,0:39:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what it's all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.67,0:39:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.67,0:39:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what it's all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.67,0:39:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I think
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.67,0:39:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what it's all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.67,0:39:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I think
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.67,0:39:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what I think
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.67,0:39:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and it will save millions more.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.67,0:39:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So that one incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.67,0:39:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which I never calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.67,0:39:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's obviously
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.67,0:39:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,over 700 or so,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.67,0:39:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,radiated out
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.67,0:39:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,through all of society.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.67,0:39:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.67,0:39:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.67,0:39:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.67,0:39:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,who reaches a high level.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.67,0:40:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill W. himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.67,0:40:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,who was an atheist,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.67,0:40:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly went
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.67,0:40:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,into the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.76,0:40:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and through him
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.76,0:40:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,radiated sufficient energy
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.76,0:40:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,for millions of people
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.76,0:40:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to recover
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.89,0:40:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,from hopeless diseases
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.09,0:40:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of all kinds.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.02,0:40:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.02,0:40:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,principles of spiritual honesty are now utilized
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.28,0:40:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in many of man's disorders, from anger management, from
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.88,0:40:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,child molestation, to all
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.50,0:40:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,kinds of acts of brutality and hopeless sociological
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.82,0:40:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,disorders. So what the person who
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.50,0:40:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,enters a 12-step group is really hoping for is the miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.74,0:40:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And because
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.74,0:40:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,AA calibrates at 540, the miraculous is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.36,0:40:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,quite possible, and it happens with sufficient frequency
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.96,0:40:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's become the greatest organization of its kind in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.60,0:41:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the energy field of AA that calibrates at 540. So once the person
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.82,0:41:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,attends the meeting and links up psychically with the group,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.52,0:41:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they recover. They recover because of the field. The person
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.00,0:41:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,himself is probably about 140.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.18,0:41:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,140, but
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.22,0:41:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.42,0:41:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,field is 540. So he's sustained by the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.24,0:41:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,field. But that is not his own level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.18,0:41:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a borrowed level. So he's under the protective umbrella of the group
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.86,0:41:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,karma, the group consciousness. So as long as he stays aligned and committed with
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.14,0:41:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the group, the sobriety persists without any energy or
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.10,0:41:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,effort. The person never even thinks of a drink. Life is smooth, beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.01,0:41:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the ego comes back and says, you don't need AA anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.59,0:41:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore he walks away
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.29,0:41:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,from the 540. If the energy field of the recovered person
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.70,0:41:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is over 540, he doesn't need to go to meetings anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.30,0:41:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But if it's under 540, which is the great likelihood, probably 99.9% of the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.56,0:42:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the minute he walks away from the group, he relapses.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.70,0:42:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the agony is worse. So because the more advanced you are
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.76,0:42:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritually, the more grave is the consequence of a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.44,0:42:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,As one progresses spiritually, how does one distinguish
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.44,0:42:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,revelation from ego creation?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.32,0:42:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego creation. Well, revelation is a peculiar experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.07,0:42:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like advanced intuition in a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.74,0:42:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, it's nonverbal. The ego verbalizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.01,0:42:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a nonverbal knowingness which arises spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.37,0:42:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,from the field. It's a knowingness. It's G-N-O-S-I-S.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.90,0:42:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It arises from the field. From the ego, it's arising from the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.32,0:43:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,From here. From here, it arises in form, in logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.22,0:43:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The knowingness has no words to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.73,0:43:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,One time, in walking out in the field, it suddenly came out of nowhere
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.79,0:43:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,because there was no thinking about it, like the revelation
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.07,0:43:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of the totality of human suffering throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.37,0:43:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The totality of the all of it, allness of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.79,0:43:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of such immense dimension that it cannot be described even at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.22,0:43:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the knowingness of it, like a great overwhelming,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.24,0:43:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,as we call those things before a tornado,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.52,0:43:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,a knowingness that revealed itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.66,0:43:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In that moment, this intense devotee, because I was an intense Christian,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.45,0:43:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,an acolyte, a boy soprano, all the rest,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.18,0:44:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly, the belief in God went, disappeared just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.08,0:44:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Any God that could allow the totality of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.69,0:44:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because I thought God created that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.55,0:44:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I held God responsible for the total agony
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.68,0:44:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of the creation of the collective consciousness of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.30,0:44:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,A grave spiritual mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.40,0:44:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And that knowingness, that it was the ego that created the total suffering of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.43,0:44:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and not God, was like telepathically transmitted.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.69,0:44:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that moment, the patient got up and stood and walked away like normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.81,0:44:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.37,0:44:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The nurses and all would faint when they saw all this kind of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.80,0:44:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it was neither purposeful nor intention, or was there any verbalization?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.84,0:45:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, the bringing forth of that awareness was itself spontaneous and non-verbal.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.68,0:45:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no verbalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.78,0:45:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like the presentation of a picture,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.72,0:45:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and the patient's own spirit saw the picture and forgave God and came out of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.56,0:45:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when they came in, they were...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.56,0:45:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It was their moment of salvation from hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.48,0:45:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, realization, revelation, occurs of its own energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.70,0:45:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.60,0:45:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.78,0:45:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not something you seek and find.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.54,0:45:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.39,0:45:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's a gift, one can take no credit for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.16,0:45:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you were thinking about squirrels, maybe, at the moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.36,0:45:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of a sudden, all of that disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.39,0:45:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And the infinite presence of God...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.71,0:46:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,God reveals itself, as though everything is turned down into technicolor and three dimension,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.31,0:46:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and the significance and the meaning and the reality of that which it is
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.51,0:46:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because all stands forth as an expression of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.38,0:46:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes forth of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.52,0:46:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If it comes from the ego, there's a thinkingness that precedes it or accompanies it,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.84,0:46:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or there's a verbalization of which I've just said I've put into words,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.50,0:46:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but the experience of it is totally wordless.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.16,0:46:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.44,0:46:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.62,0:46:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,look at the beauty of a setting sun. There's no words about it. In fact, anything you can say
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.50,0:46:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,about it is an enormous detraction. It's just a total experience of stunning beauty, which has
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.70,0:46:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,no words for it. What is a parent's responsibility, and what can parents do in guiding their children
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.34,0:46:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,about the violence in video games and TV and all of that? That's a tough one. I'm very glad I don't
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.79,0:47:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,have children right now. Huh? Society is being attacked in two dimensions. It's only the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.40,0:47:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual power of groups such as this to prevent it from being destroyed. It gets it from the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.08,0:47:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Luciferic by the distortion of logic and reason and misrepresentation of facts and demonization
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.00,0:47:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which is integrous, as we saw this morning when we calibrated some of those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.43,0:47:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets it from the Luciferic by the distortion of logic and reason and misrepresentation of facts
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.73,0:47:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets it from the satanic energy, which is that of violence, seduction, rape, beheading people,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.73,0:47:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,serial murder, the joy of killing. It's sometimes expressed quite subtly. I was quite dismayed to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.82,0:48:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,find a new woman's group called BOW. And the purpose of the group was to learn how to go out
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.24,0:48:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in the field with shotguns and kill pheasants and be just like men. The number of fallacies
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.35,0:48:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,involved there is stacked upon each other, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.13,0:48:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, they picked, if that is supposedly masculine, its lowest expression. If you want
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.64,0:48:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to be like a man, don't pick its lowest denominator. Try to pick the highest. They picked the lowest
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.08,0:48:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,denominator because the women were enjoying the death of the pheasants. In fact, they
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.10,0:48:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,were practicing holding the pheasant in their hands as it took 15 minutes to die. And sharing
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.56,0:48:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of feeling its squirming death spasms. I thought, this is, man, grotesque.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.42,0:48:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, really grotesque. And cloaked in the idea of, first of all, that the feminine
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.86,0:49:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is inferior to the masculine, which is bizarre and a delusional distortion of truth to begin
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.26,0:49:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,with, you know? Why rise above that which you are not? So that's a false straw man to
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.88,0:49:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,begin with. In the world I grew up in, nobody ever considered a woman less than a man that
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.22,0:49:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I ever noticed. If you say anything disrespectful in front of your grandmother, God help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.01,0:49:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you who ranked in the home. Frank, Frank, don't, your, the drapes. My grandfather
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.29,0:49:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,walked through and he hid his pipe like this. He walked through the living room. My grandmother
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.67,0:49:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,would be after him, Frank, Frank, the drapes. And then she'd wave the drapes and she'd want
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.11,0:49:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the smoke in the drapes, you know? He was confined to his smoking room, you know what
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.85,0:49:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm saying? So the illusion there was a socioeconomic distortion because she wasn't out in the workplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.66,0:49:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, she wasn't supposed to be out in the workplace. She was supposed to be out in the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.52,0:49:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,workplace. You'd die of shame if your wife had to go to work. And I don't know if a single
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.26,0:49:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,woman is interested in a job. She'd feel very badly for the poor old spinster lady who has
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.60,0:50:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to work. So we grew into that which was the social expectation of the time. Each one of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.17,0:50:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,us perfectly fulfilled whatever was the expectation of the time. One thing was not better than
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.37,0:50:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,another. What was the question? Huh? What? Huh? Good idea. So, you know, we grew into
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.80,0:50:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that. I don't know. Maybe, maybe a little. Is the calibration that you come into the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.76,0:50:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,world with the one you left in your last incarnation? I never asked that. I would assume it's that
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.66,0:50:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you spent some time in the inner planes and could have made some progress there. I don't
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.96,0:50:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,know. I never asked that. I don't even know if we have permission to ask that. Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.53,0:51:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask that in public. Okay. Between lifetimes, one has the opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.47,0:51:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,for spiritual advancement or resistance. I guess we have the opportunity for spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.26,0:51:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,advancement. Yeah. I don't know. What does healthy sexuality look like? Look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.20,0:51:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like a lot of fun, if you ask me. People wonder what sexuality calibrates. It calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.06,0:51:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,about 205. Also, money calibrates 205. So it seems that that which is necessary for
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.80,0:51:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,physical survival and the expression of physical survival, that's what it's all about. And
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.80,0:51:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what it's all about. That's what it's all about. That's what it's all about. That's
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.88,0:52:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,going to take years. So it's true there's a lot of money in order to pay for it. When
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.22,0:52:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you see what it is, you're going to need money. So the current era, what's what we mean
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.38,0:52:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,by a reward model, that's how you your future self is going to be seeing. I read a book
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.57,0:52:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,about someone called Gal Gadot in a very sóящing and very obrigado lecture about
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.11,0:52:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,howeds, however, were интерpreting andCHOL Poland is one of. So it was a really amazing
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.41,0:52:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,lecture. It was a stuff I really, really wanted to read. Yeah, everyone made me a lot of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.99,0:52:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very exciting. Yeah, after the Great Depression, everything had to be change. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.65,0:52:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a beneficence to each other, like a blessing to each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.96,0:52:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,a reaffirmation of loving each other, you see, intimacy and closeness.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.82,0:52:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When it becomes a pursuit, driving a person, then you're being run by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.38,0:52:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So anything, collecting antiques is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.04,0:52:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be run by it, you know, collecting panties.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.34,0:53:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So these things are amusements, they're proclivities, they're hobbies.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.66,0:53:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So the traditional view is that the downside of anything is one's attachment to it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.38,0:53:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ascribing of magical qualities to that,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.84,0:53:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which is...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.02,0:53:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which is not so, it's only a projection, a glamorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.85,0:53:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we see is the glamorization and the exploitation of sexuality,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.69,0:53:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a different story than actual sexuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.54,0:53:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Actual sexuality is certainly a delightful pleasure,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.20,0:54:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,without which there would be no human beings on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.20,0:54:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Be the end of the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.66,0:54:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So I guess it must be okay or we wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.91,0:54:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Created by God and the physicality,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.14,0:54:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,then, is merely the expression of a physical craving or an emotional commitment.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.65,0:54:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So it can be one of many things.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.96,0:54:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, everything is...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.88,0:54:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the karmic consequence of everything is determined by the spiritual intention behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.60,0:54:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So it isn't the sexuality, it's the spiritual intention behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.13,0:54:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,To exploit the weak, to take advantage of people,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.93,0:54:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to slip them sleeping pills and have violent sex with them while they're unconscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.95,0:54:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,are obviously...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.07,0:54:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,severe perversions of what should be a natural instinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.16,0:54:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.09,0:54:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and people in spiritual work go through a couple of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.09,0:54:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,First comes vegetarianism, and then the next comes celibacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.67,0:55:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think celibacy and vegetarianism are wonderful, and you should do them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.50,0:55:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did everybody leave the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.28,0:55:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of its meaning to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.28,0:55:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think that you're killing,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.28,0:55:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, if you believe in death, then you think that this animal is being killed for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.28,0:55:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you can't kill it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.28,0:55:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't eat an animal because you believe in death.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.28,0:55:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You think it just died.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.12,0:55:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Same with sexuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.12,0:55:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think it's evil, and et cetera, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.15,0:55:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So these things, as you evolve in consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.15,0:55:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,have different meanings and significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.15,0:55:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't say anything's right or wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.15,0:55:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You can say, does it serve your spiritual progress at this point,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.15,0:55:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,or does it not serve it?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.15,0:55:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There may be a point at which you feel guilty about sex, and it's not serving it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.47,0:55:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,However, then you have to get off the...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.47,0:55:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,guilt about the sexuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.47,0:56:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So the same with thinking that you're killing things in order to...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.82,0:56:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to eat them.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.54,0:56:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Killing pheasants for fun is like shooting prairie dogs for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.54,0:56:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's a perversion of the sporting instinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.64,0:56:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, like every other animal,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.64,0:56:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,has sort of an innate desire to kill things,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.92,0:56:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's one of the things we transcend.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.82,0:56:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When you think that 40 million buffalo roam the plains,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.04,0:56:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's not one left.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.30,0:56:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Not one.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.36,0:56:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd say, out of 40 million?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.49,0:56:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There's got to be one buffalo somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.49,0:56:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We hunted all over Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.16,0:56:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't find one?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.16,0:56:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All over Yavapai County.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.42,0:56:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All over Arizona.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.64,0:56:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of 40 million magnificent creatures,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.74,0:56:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,man did not leave even one?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.87,0:56:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not one wild buffalo left.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.87,0:57:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Not one.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.35,0:57:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you do if it's obvious that many of your immediate...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.35,0:57:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and extended family members are below 200?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.69,0:57:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.69,0:57:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You're adopted.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.69,0:57:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it is a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.17,0:57:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a problem, especially in 12-step groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.17,0:57:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,One person is forced by the severity of the calamity
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.33,0:57:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to join a spiritual group,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.68,0:57:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and they are obligated to become
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.68,0:57:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,intensely more spiritual or die.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.94,0:57:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Under the duress of either you surrender to God
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.94,0:57:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and learn to be honest, et cetera, or croak,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.74,0:57:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of people choose God.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.74,0:57:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They then become quite spiritually oriented.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.70,0:57:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They start talking about easy does it,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.70,0:57:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,live and let live, first things first,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.70,0:58:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,forgive instead of revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.83,0:58:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And this can put you at considerable disparity,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.83,0:58:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and it certainly leads to divorce very often.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.83,0:58:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If only one member of the family starts getting committed
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.27,0:58:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to spiritual evolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.27,0:58:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,there may be considerable disparity
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.27,0:58:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,with other members of the family,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.27,0:58:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is a frequent cause of divorce, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.27,0:58:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If salvation and enlightenment both lead to the same end
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.76,0:58:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and enlightenment is a more demanding road to follow,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.76,0:58:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the reason one would focus
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.76,0:58:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,on the path of enlightenment?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.85,0:58:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we explained earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.85,0:58:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,salvation and enlightenment are two different things.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.85,0:58:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Salvation means to reach the level of love,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.85,0:58:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,especially unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.85,0:58:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.00,0:58:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you're looking at 800 to 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.00,0:58:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Enlightenment is just as more advanced,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.61,0:58:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,more difficult, more arduous,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.61,0:58:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and extremely difficult to,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.71,0:59:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely difficult on this planet now.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.82,0:59:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's extremely difficult,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.98,0:59:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,it's extremely difficult to get to 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.33,0:59:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,To get beyond 600, we said, happens 1 in 10 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.40,0:59:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,To get to 700 is less than even that.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.13,0:59:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,To go beyond that is practically never happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.13,0:59:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Centuries and centuries go by
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.48,0:59:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,without a single individual going that high.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.58,0:59:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they do reach such levels,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.58,0:59:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it is extremely arduous.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.68,0:59:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Without special help and special inside knowledge,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.68,0:59:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,one would never make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.68,0:59:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And thankfully, the Buddha described what it was like,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.16,0:59:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that his bones felt like they were being broken,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.16,0:59:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and Christ's sweat, blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.79,0:59:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, the human nervous system
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.17,0:59:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is not really made for anything beyond 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.30,0:59:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,540 to 600 is not made for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.30,0:59:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And under special conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.30,1:00:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,with an intensity of rock-hard steel-like,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.94,1:00:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,immutable commitment,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.94,1:00:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.68,1:00:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, it must be a rather unique,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.68,1:00:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,peculiar thing to do, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.78,1:00:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times has anybody reached
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.78,1:00:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,over 850, 900 in man's history?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.13,1:00:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, only occasional centuries go by.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.32,1:00:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it has to do with the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.06,1:00:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it chooses to express itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.06,1:00:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with commitments that were karmically made
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.19,1:00:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and willingness to be of service to God no matter what,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.56,1:00:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond the ordinary, beyond the ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.68,1:00:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows why?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.15,1:00:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we'll stop. One more question.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.15,1:01:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What can you do for your children?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.39,1:01:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that question was there.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.48,1:01:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the best way to educate children
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.48,1:01:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in public schools or mass private schools,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.48,1:01:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to teach the Old Testament and other religious fallacies?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.96,1:01:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the best way to teach questions
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.96,1:01:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that are about children and families?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.28,1:01:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, well, it's no different than one's own individual.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.28,1:01:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with picking what you think
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.28,1:01:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is the most truthful, beneficial pathway to God
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.78,1:01:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and sharing it with the children.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.78,1:01:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The children are going to learn in school
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.85,1:01:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,things that are considerably different.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.52,1:01:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many laws and rules that come,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.52,1:01:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,laws and rules and belief systems
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.52,1:01:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that are inculcated into behaviors and laws
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.32,1:01:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that come out of books of the Bible
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.32,1:01:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that we found were below 200, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.32,1:02:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.71,1:02:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is fallacious is now the law of the land.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.71,1:02:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So what can you do about that?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.93,1:02:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you're only responsible for the evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.93,1:02:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of your own consciousness, and in so doing,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.93,1:02:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you lift others.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.03,1:02:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So I would say you become the most beneficent,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.03,1:02:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,loving, forgiving, compassionate being you can be,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.03,1:02:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and thereby inspire the children.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.03,1:02:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the children are at the same time
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.35,1:02:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,under the pressure of MTV and fallacies
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.35,1:02:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of both Luciferic and Satanic dimensions,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.38,1:02:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,seduction by a perverse sexuality,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.38,1:02:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the profanation of the sacred.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.17,1:02:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,One can watch the extremely erotic,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.68,1:02:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,glamorized images seductively displayed,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.68,1:02:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with very advanced and a unique technology
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.46,1:03:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to capture the energy of the viewer,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.36,1:03:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,who is then attracted by that which is deleterious.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.55,1:03:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The perverse seduction, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.55,1:03:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is to pull into a certain energy field
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.84,1:03:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is deleterious spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.84,1:03:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and the field then dominates you,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.84,1:03:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and you become its servant and victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.56,1:03:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So the downside
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.24,1:03:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of our current society is severe.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.24,1:03:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The distortion of reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.24,1:03:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,which is presented as truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.23,1:03:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the seduction of such things as video games.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.03,1:03:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When you hear what the story is
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.03,1:03:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,behind a certain video game,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.03,1:03:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you say, nobody in their right mind would buy it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.70,1:03:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a big seller.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.31,1:03:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A big seller.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.50,1:03:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,To track down, rape, murder, seduce,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.98,1:03:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,rape and murder a lady,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.98,1:04:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and take her money.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.68,1:04:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what a gallant image for manhood, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.68,1:04:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly different than the image of
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.75,1:04:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity that we grew up with.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.94,1:04:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's the biggest seller there is.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.94,1:04:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Theft Auto 3.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.94,1:04:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a newer one out,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.55,1:04:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,far more wicked than that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.55,1:04:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 70.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.99,1:04:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,70.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.78,1:04:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So the child is being brainwashed with that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.81,1:04:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And certainly being a parent today
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.81,1:04:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is scary.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.00,1:04:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you've got to counter that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.13,1:04:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So you counter it by the presentation of truth
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.13,1:04:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,as you know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.13,1:04:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And try to surround them with a culture
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.13,1:04:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that respects love,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.13,1:04:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and the dignity of man,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.13,1:04:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and the dignity of woman, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.45,1:04:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And hopefully by identification
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.74,1:04:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,with that which you are,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.74,1:04:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and by the power of that which you have become,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.74,1:05:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they will choose that.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.44,1:05:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, however,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.44,1:05:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they have their own karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.44,1:05:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And the most difficult part of being a parent
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.44,1:05:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is to surrender them to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.44,1:05:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Their salvation is not up to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.83,1:05:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And consequently,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.89,1:05:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you play a part in their life,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.18,1:05:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,hopefully, positive in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.18,1:05:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But from that point on,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.18,1:05:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,they're really on their own.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.63,1:05:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So I myself was guided, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.63,1:05:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to High Episcopal Church.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.04,1:05:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,My great-grandfather was the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.04,1:05:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Episcopal Bishop in Milwaukee.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.52,1:05:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had the most
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.52,1:05:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,what you would say,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.93,1:05:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,ethical, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.19,1:05:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,being an acolyte in the choir
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.19,1:05:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of a great high episcopal cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.19,1:05:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Part of the choir,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.35,1:05:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and the music, and the pageantry
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.35,1:05:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,was as uplifting and beautiful,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.35,1:05:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the beatitude, the beauty of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.44,1:06:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The stained glass windows,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.44,1:06:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the incense, the pageantry.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.18,1:06:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It was incredible.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.18,1:06:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Incredibly magnificent and beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.18,1:06:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And 10 or 15 years later,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.26,1:06:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I became an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.39,1:06:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor mom and dad.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.58,1:06:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They never knew it, thank God.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.58,1:06:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,God took them away
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.58,1:06:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,out of his mercy, of their mercy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.58,1:06:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So they did know it for a while,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.58,1:06:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and my father was quite distressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.58,1:06:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.87,1:06:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet what happened to the atheism
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.87,1:06:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,was it led to the pits of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.87,1:06:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the pits of hell,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.87,1:06:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the entity said,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.87,1:06:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is a God,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.87,1:06:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,ask him to help me.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.19,1:06:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And then,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.22,1:06:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,unconsciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.22,1:06:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and non-consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.41,1:06:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the opening
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.86,1:06:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of divine revelation,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.86,1:06:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and the transformation
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.76,1:06:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to which you witness to this day.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.30,1:06:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So how could a parent have helped?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.30,1:07:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.86,1:07:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,On this hand,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.86,1:07:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and on this hand,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.86,1:07:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and on this hand,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.86,1:07:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but then this came out of the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.86,1:07:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,reality of the presence of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.86,1:07:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And so what happens with the children
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.86,1:07:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is maybe 5% what you do,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.24,1:07:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and 95% karma,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.31,1:07:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and 5% the environment.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.60,1:07:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So we pray for direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.60,1:07:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We ask for God's help
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.60,1:07:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,for ourselves as parents.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.60,1:07:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We ask for the guidance of our children.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.60,1:07:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And we do all within His power.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.60,1:07:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.60,1:07:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you're only answerable to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.60,1:07:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Only you know
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.60,1:07:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've done what you can
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.60,1:07:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,on their behalf.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.72,1:07:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,As a physician,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.72,1:07:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sometimes
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.72,1:07:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,presented.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.72,1:07:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is the sick patient.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.72,1:07:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know something
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.72,1:07:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that is not within
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.72,1:07:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,traditional medical approval
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.40,1:07:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,at the moment,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.40,1:07:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but I know it will help
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.40,1:07:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the patient recover.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.40,1:07:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So at that moment,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.40,1:07:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to decide,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.40,1:07:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,am I going to be answerable
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.40,1:07:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to my colleagues
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.40,1:08:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and popularity with my colleagues,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.40,1:08:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or am I going to help this patient
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.40,1:08:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,who without this
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.40,1:08:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is certainly going to die?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.56,1:08:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that moment,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.56,1:08:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you decide,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.56,1:08:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,on death's bed,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.56,1:08:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to be answerable
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.56,1:08:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to God for what you did
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.56,1:08:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,with this patient.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.56,1:08:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Your colleagues are not going
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.64,1:08:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to be at your deathbed
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.64,1:08:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to cheer you on
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.64,1:08:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as our favorite colleague.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.64,1:08:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.37,1:08:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The reality of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.60,1:08:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you're answerable then,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.60,1:08:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,only to yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.60,1:08:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing that in the presence of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.60,1:08:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth is what you must live by.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.04,1:08:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You must know that to yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.30,1:08:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you have done all you can
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.30,1:08:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to help these children
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.30,1:08:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in the best way you know the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.30,1:08:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think that's all
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.46,1:08:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we're answerable for.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.28,1:08:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We have,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.30,1:09:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we have ten after four.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.84,1:09:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want Nico
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.84,1:09:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to chant for five minutes?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.10,1:09:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'll stop
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.10,1:09:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and anybody who wants
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.10,1:09:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to say hello can say hello
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.10,1:09:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll sign any books.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.36,1:09:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.36,1:09:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,get ready.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.54,1:09:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Buckle your seat buckles.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.44,1:09:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.44,1:09:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.44,1:10:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.44,1:10:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.44,1:10:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.44,1:10:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.44,1:10:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.44,1:10:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.44,1:10:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.44,1:10:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.44,1:10:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.44,1:10:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.44,1:10:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.44,1:10:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.44,1:10:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.44,1:11:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.02,1:11:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.02,1:12:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.02,1:13:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.18,1:13:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, and we're glad to greet anyone who wishes to say hello to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.59,1:13:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we have to turn this off somehow.
